    About us

    The Honeycomb Racing Way

    The strength of our team comes from our dedication to our core values in everything we do, from voluntary work to the engineering behind our car.

    Sustainability

    We believe in ensuring we make a positive impact, not only on those we work with, but also on the environment and our local community.

    Cooperation

    Honeycomb Racing isn’t just the four of us – it’s a collective of everyone who’s ever supported us, and we never want to forget that.

    Innovation

    Working by the book is boring – we’re always looking for new solutions to old problems that can give us the edge over our competition.

    What we’ve done

    Our Achievements

    Despite this being our first season competing, we’ve already managed to make a splash, collecting 7 trophies across Regionals and Nationals.

    Scottish Regionals

    Fastest Car

    Award

    With a time of 1.123 seconds, we made Scotland’s fastest car at our first Regionals. A large part of this was thanks to our bearing sponsor, Carter Bearings, who have aided the past 3 UK Champions.

    Scottish Regionals

    Best Engineered Car Award

    Following on from our breath-taking time, we also managed to snag the award of best engineered car in Scotland, which is a true testament to how great our engineering team is.

    Scottish Regionals

    Scottish Regional Champions

    With the amazing success of our car, as well as several nominations for other awards, we managed to become the Scottish Regional Champions at our first ever Regionals, setting us for great success at Nationals.

    UK Nationals

    Fastest Car

    Award

    Repeating our success at Regionals, we once again managed to engineer the fastest car, but this time in the UK. With a time of 1.15 seconds, we blew away the competition on day 2, and managed to get one of the most prestigious awards of the competition.

    UK Nationals

    Best Verbal Presentation Award

    Managing to convey our enthusiasm and passion for the project, our verbal presentation was good enough to snatch us the verbal presentation award, which was especially exciting considering how nervous we’d been for it beforehand.

    UK Nationals

    Scottish National Champions (UK 2nd)

    For the first time in over a decade, a Scottish team made it to the podium of the UK National Finals, and it was us! This also resulted in us getting the title of Scottish National Champions, and being given a ticket to compete at the World Finals in Singapore.
